rooms.Name: Standing over an opening in the earth.
rooms.Description:
Your mission is simple.  Find your way through the maze below. Sounds easy
enough.

rooms.Name: The endless Quest Maze
rooms.Description:
All the tunnels down here look the same.  The same smooth granite walls run
in all directions.  There are old rusted lanterns hanging from large wooden
beams that support the ceiling.  Doesn't look like there's been anyone here
in a very long time.  Briefly pausing to ponder your own sanity, you press
onward.

rooms.Name: Front lawn of the White House
rooms.Description:
No sudden moves here.  Don't even spit on the grass.  The whole area is
crawling with secret service agents.  What a majestic view of the White
house.  Go on, salute the flag and show some patriotism.

rooms.Name: Front lawn of the White House
rooms.Description:
No sudden moves here.  Don't even spit on the grass.  The whole area is
crawling with secret service agents.  What a majestic view of the White
house.  Go on, salute the flag and show some patriotism.

rooms.Name: Grand entrance of the White House
rooms.Description:
Look the front door is left unlocked.  Bill must be expecting guests *wink*.
Go on in.  Heck, it's your tax money that keeps this place running. Grab a
beer out of the fridge and find a comfy chair.

rooms.Name: Hallway in the White House
rooms.Description:
Oh now this is nice.  Not a thing is out of place and the place is quiet as a
mouse.  Hah! Boogie on up to the oval office and pretend you're president.

rooms.Name: Hallway in the White House
rooms.Description:
Oh now this is nice.  Not a thing is out of place and the place is quiet as a
mouse.  Hah! Boogie on up to the oval office and pretend you're president.

Exits.Description: Take off your shoes before you start up that staircase.

rooms.Name: A guest bedroom in the White House
rooms.Description:
Often close friends of the first family stay for extended periods and these
bedrooms are for their use.  And then again, sometimes they stay only a few
moments and still utilize these rooms.

rooms.Name: The Presidential Washroom
rooms.Description:
Wonder where all those thousand dollar toilets seats are that the government
buys?  Well they're right here =)

rooms.Name: The Oval Office
rooms.Description:
This is where all the important decisions for the whole world are made. That
familiar desk, paintings, flags and carpet...it's all here.  Oops, Clinton's
here too.

Exits.Description: Careful not to trip and fall down the staircase.

rooms.Name: Light at the end of the tunnel
rooms.Description: You made it to the end of the quest!
